GATEWAY.Definition: a place through which you have to go to get to another place, esp. a tall and wide entrance through a wall

SOUL.Definition: the spiritual part of a person that some people believe continues to exist in some form after their body has died, or the part of a person that is not physical and experiences deep feelings and emotions

COME OUT OF.Definition: the spiritual part of a person that some people believe continues to exist in some form after their body has died, or the part of a person that is not physical and experiences deep feelings and emotions

FEEDING.Definition: to give food to a person, group, or animal

MANUFACTURING.Definition: to produce goods in large numbers, usually in a factory using machines

SEEDS.Definition: a small, round, or oval object produced by a plant and from which, when it is planted, a new plant can grow

PLANT.Definition: (in this context) a verb that means to put a plant into the ground or into a container of soil so that it will grow

HARVEST.Definition: the activity or time of gathering a crop, or a crop that is gathered

CONSUME.Definition: (in this context) to eat or drink, especially a lot of something

BE IN GOOD SHAPE.Definition: to be prepared and ready to do something (in this case, physically)

ORGAN.Definition: a part of the body of an animal or plant that performs a particular job

AS IF.Definition: as would be the case if

NEGLECTED.Definition: not receiving enough care or attention

INDULGE.Definition: to allow yourself or another person to have something enjoyable, especially more than is good for you

STRANGER.Definition: A fragile object is easily damaged or broken

FRAGILE.Definition: A fragile object is easily damaged or broken

UNDERPRIVILEGED.Definition: without the money, possessions, education, opportunities, etc. that the average person has

ADVANTAGE.Definition: a condition giving a greater chance of success

ENDLESS.Definition: never finishing, or seeming never to finish

HARMFUL.Definition: Causing physical or other injury or damage

CHILLING.Definition: Relaxing, not doing anything in particular

CRAM.Definition: (in this context) to try to learn a lot very quickly before an exam

USELESS.Definition: of no use; not working or not achieving what is needed

BULLSHIT.Definition: stupid or untrue talk or writing; nonsense.

VOLUNTARILY.Definition: in a voluntary way (= done, made, or given willingly)

AT YOUR DISPOSAL.Definition: in a voluntary way (= done, made, or given willingly)

SUPPLY AND DEMAND.Definition: the amount of a commodity, product, or service available and the desire of buyers for it, considered as factors regulating its price.

TAKE A BREAK.Definition: to stop doing something for a short period of time: to rest

SCROLLING.Definition: the action of moving displayed text or graphics up, down, or across on a computer screen in order to view different parts of them.

INJECTING.Definition: to use a needle and syringe (= small tube) to put a liquid such as a drug into a person's body

DIGESTING.Definition: to change food in your stomach into substances that your body can use

NUTRIENTS.Definition: any substance that plants or animals need in order to live and grow

HERD.Definition: A group of cattle or other large herbivorous mammals of a single kind kept together for a specific purpose.

WORTH.Definition: sufficiently good, enjoyable, or successful to repay any effort, trouble, or expense.
